  "description": [
    "Page Two In Harlem Twenty Years Ago This Week Vacation days for the boys and girls will come to an end next Monday when the school bell will call them to their studies for another nine months Owing to the fact that the new build ing is not completed the whole school will be organized in the old build ing for the present It will probably be a month before the new building is ready Following is the list of teachers R E Story superintendent M Eugenia Story Rose Cashman Bessie Fuller Stella Alverson and John E Bakke high school Hazel Bolfe Effie Edmonds Neva Dodge Melissa M Lane Nora Cashman grade school Mrs A A Ekegren substitute There was a light vote case at the special election held in the county Tuesday to vote on road bonds and seed grain Only 84 votes were cast in Harlem 15 votes being cast against seed grain and 7 against road bonds Albert Anderson says there is no truth in the stories which have been circulated that there are no crops on the Second Bench He proved the statement by bringing in some sample ears of finely matured com He has two"
